- VSCode Version: 1.8.1

Today we can specify json schemas:

```js
{
  "json.schemas": [
    {
      "fileMatch": [
        "tsconfig.*.json"
      ],
      "url": "http://json.schemastore.org/tsconfig"
    }
  ]
}
```

It would be great we can extend a schema to provide additional fields:

```js
{
  "json.schemas": [
    {
      "fileMatch": [
        "package.json"
      ],
      "url": [ "http://json.schemastore.org/package", "./avajs.schema.json", "./nyc.schema.json"]
    }
  ]
}
```

Or is there a way to extend (multiple inherits) a schema with the json schema syntax?

```js
{
  "json.schemas": [
    {
      "fileMatch": [
        "package.json"
      ],
      "url": "./my.package.schema.json"]
    }
  ]
}
```

```js
// my.pacakge.schema.json
{
   // merging "http://json.schemastore.org/package", "./avajs.schema.json", "./nyc.schema.json"
}
```

- VSCode Version: 1.8.1
- OS Version: macOS Sierra 10.12.2, Windows 10

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Copy the code below into a .js file and open it in VSCode.
2. Hover over method2 to see that it only shows "any" and Go to Definition, Peek Definition, Find all References do not work. It also does not appear in the definition of the "bob" object when hovering over it. However, it does appear in autocomplete.


```
// A simple object constructor function.
function Person() {
    this.method1 = function() {}
}
var bob = new Person();

// Intellisense appears to work for a predefined object method.
// Hovering over the method shows the correct function signature: "(property) Person.method1: () => void".
// Go to Definition, Peek Definition, Find all References work just fine.
// Appears correctly in auto complete.
bob.method1();

// Add an object method dynamically.
// Intellisense appears to work only partially for a dynamically added object method.
// Hovering over the method just shows "any".
// Go to Definition, Peek Definition, Find all References DO NOT work.
// BUT it does appear correctly in auto complete.
bob.method2 = function() {}
bob.method2();

// Add a prototype method dynamically.
// Hovering over the method shows the correct function signature: "(property) Person.method3: () => void".
// Go to Definition, Peek Definition, Find all References work just fine.
// Appears correctly in auto complete.
Person.prototype.method3 = function() {}
bob.method3();
```
